    "aiContext":  {
                      "prompt":  "Choose each eligible Tiny unattended nonmagical object to animate; while servants remain within 120 feet, offer the caster a Bonus Action command for one, any, or all controlled servants.",
                      "playerInputRequired":  true
                  },
    "description":  "You touch one Tiny, nonmagical object that isn\u0027t attached to another object or a surface and isn\u0027t being carried by another creature. The target animates and sprouts little arms and legs, becoming a creature under your control until the spell ends or the creature drops to 0 hit points. See Tiny Servant for its statistics. As a bonus action, you can mentally command the creature if it is within 120 feet of you. (If you control multiple creatures with this spell, you can command any or all of them at the same time, issuing the same command to each one.) You decide what action the creature will take and where it will move during its next turn, or you can issue a simple, general command, such as to fetch a key, stand watch, or stack some books. If you issue no commands, the servant does nothing other than defend itself against hostile creatures. Once given an order, the servant continues to follow that order until its task is complete. When the creature drops to 0 hit points, it reverts to its original form, and any remaining damage carries over to that form.",
    "higherLevels":  "When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can animate two additional objects for each slot level above 3rd.",
